snippet.title: install-nothing: a tiny Rust-based terminal app that simulates installing  #github
snippet.description:
install-nothing is a tiny Rust-based terminal app that simulates installing… well… nothing. Run it, and you’ll get progress bars, fake logs, pretend package lists — the whole ‘installing things’ vibe — without actually changing anything on your system. 

It’s playful, and licensed under the extremely permissive ‘do whatever you want with it’ license. If you love terminal toys, want a fun demo app, or just enjoy confusing your coworkers, install-nothing is a perfect little Rust project to star.

#github #opensource
